{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀναφαίνω</b>, <br /> <i>poetry</i> ἀμφ-: <i>future</i> -φᾰνῶ, but <b>-φᾱνῶ</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 528 codices (-φαίνω 2nd-3rd c.AD: Hermes Trismegistus): \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> ἀνέφηνα, Hellenistic -έφᾱνα: <i>perfect</i> -πέφηνα late, Ps.-[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Philopatr.” 3\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<b>cause to give light, make to blaze up,</b> ξύλα, δαΐδας[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.310. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>bring to light, produce,</b> ὄφιας[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4. 105. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> <b>show forth, make known, display,</b> θεοπροπίας, ἀρετήν, ἐπεσβολίας, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.87, 20.411, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.159; πραπίδων καρπόν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 211; κἀνέφηνεν οὐ δεδειγμένα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 432.7; ἀ. θυσίας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 466; ὀργάν [prev. author] “Ba.” 538; ἄστρα 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.3.4; ἡμέρᾳ καὶ ἡλίῳ.. χάριν οἶδα ὅτι μοι Κλεινίαν ἀ. [prev. author] “Smp.” 4.12\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; rarely of sound, βοὰν ἀμφ. <b>send forth a loud</b> cry, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 829; ἀ. μελέων νόμους 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 745\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—in <i>middle</i>, νίκαν ἀνεφάνατο[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 4(3).71. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>proclaim, declare,</b> βασιλέα ἀ. τινά[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “P.” 4.62\">Refs</a>]; νικάσαις ἀνέφανε Κυράναν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 9.73, compare “N.” 9.12\">Refs</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, τοὺς πολίτας ἀγαθοὺς ὄντας ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 108c: with \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, ἀναφαίνω σε τόδε.. ὀνομάζειν I <b>proclaim that</b> they call thee by this name, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 528:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>middle</i>, in <i>Doric dialect</i> form ἀμφ-, <b>adopt</b> as one's son, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Leg.Gort.” 10.34, +others \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__3.b</b></Level4> of things, <b>appoint, institute,</b> ὃς τελετὰς ἀνέφηνε καὶ ὄργια[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 3.713, compare “Marm.Par.” 28; νῆσον ἀ. τινὶ οἰκεῖν 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Heroicus” 19.16. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> ἀναφάναντες τὴν Κύπρον <b>having sighted..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Acts.21.3. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> ἀναφᾰνήσομαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 950, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Parmenides” 132a, +others;\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] but also <b>-φανοῦμαι</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. author] “Plt.” 289c: \">Refs</a>]<i>perfect</i> ἀναπέφασμαι, but <b>-πέφηνα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus (see. below)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], etc.: <i>aorist</i> ἀνεφᾰνην[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 124\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>to be shown forth, appear plainly,</b> ἀναφαίνεται ἀστήρ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.62\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. αἰπὺς ὄλεθρος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 174; τῇ δεκάτῃ.. ἀνεφαίνετο πατρὶς ἄρουρα 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.29; τὸ Δέλτα ἐστὶ νεωστὶ ἀναπεφηνός 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.15, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1222 (Lyric poetry), etc.; ἀ. ὁ βλάπτων 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 328. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.b</b></Level4> <b>reappear,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.195 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of rivers which flow underground, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 6.76, 7.30\">Refs</a>]; simply, <b>spring up,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 198. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> ἀναφανῆναι μούναρχος <b>to be declared</b> king, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 3.82; στρατηγὸς ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Ion” 541e; κλέπτης τις ὁ δίκαιος.. ἀναπέφανται \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>proved to be..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “R.” 334a, compare “Smp.” 185a\">Refs</a>]; ἀ. λογογράφος ἐκ τριηράρχου from a sea-captain <b>to come out</b> a romancer, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.173\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—also with <i>participle</i>, ἀναπέφανται ὢν ἀγαθός[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 350c\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀναφαίνεσθαι ἔχων, σεσωσμένοι, <b>to be seen</b> or <b>found to</b> have, <b>to be plainly</b> in safety, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Sph.” 233c, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.2.15, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> the <i>active</i> <i>intransitive</i> in later Greek, ἀνέφαινεν ἕσπερος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Musaeus Epicus 111 (variant), compare 3rd c.AD: Heliodorus Scriptor Eroticus 5.22:—ἀναφῆναι is probably _falsa lectio_ for{ἀναφανῆναι} in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.165.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0398","accentedUnicode":"ἀναφαίνω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0303","matchingForm":"ἀνά","stepTransliteration":"ana","gloss":"each","_zh_tw_Gloss":"各","_es_Gloss":"cada uno","_zh_Gloss":"各"},{"strongNumber":"G5316","matchingForm":"φαίνω","stepTransliteration":"fainō","gloss":"to shine/appear","_zh_tw_Gloss":"顯現","_es_Gloss":"brillar/aparecer","_zh_Gloss":"显现"}],"shortDef":"to appear","mediumDef":"<b>to bring to light, display;</b>, <i>middle</i> and <i>passive</i> <b>to appear,</b> <ref='Luk.19.11'>Lk. 19:11</ref>; a nautical term, <b>to come in sight of,</b> <ref='Act.21.3'>Acts 21:3</ref>*","stepGloss":"to appear","stepTransliteration":"anafainō","count":2,"_es_Definition":"avistar, observar algo, vista; pas. aparecer","_zh_tw_Definition":"使出現, 出現(路 19:11; 徒 21:3)","_zh_Definition":"使出现, 出现(路 19:11; 徒 21:3)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"hiện lên; xuất hiện; nhìn thấy","_zh_tw_Gloss":"望見, 顯出來","_es_Gloss":"aparecer","_zh_Gloss":"望见, 显出来"}]}